<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-04-05T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-04-05T03:00:00-05:00" n="659" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d659">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">693.119/420: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-04-05T16:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">April 5,
                                        1919, 4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                    April 5, 12.15 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>My despatch number 2446, January 10.<note n="92" xml:id="d659fn92"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_291">p.
                                291</ref>.</note> The Japanese now seem ready to join in an
                            agreement against making arrangements for furnishing arms to China. I
                            shall proceed to make such an agreement with the colleagues
                            concerned.</p>
                        <p>Such restrictions might be considered to operate unfavorably to the
                            Southern and Central military who have not been supplied by the Japanese
                            as have the Northerners. But I believe that the total impossibility of
                            arms traffic will be beneficial. British Minister is of the same
                            opinion.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>